id: pmc-8ssd
title: Prepend merge promotes a stale Unreleased section into the released version instead of duplicating it (GH #47)
description: "mergeChangelog in prepend mode inserted the generated ## <version> section while leaving the prior ## Unreleased section (same items) in place, so every released CHANGELOG ended up with both. Fix: when the generated output carries a concrete version and no Unreleased section of its own, promote a leading ## Unreleased into the version it ships in (Keep a Changelog semantics), consuming it once for the newest version."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-13T19:14:47.096Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-13T19:15:55.285Z"
author: claude
resolution: "Promote a leading Unreleased section into the generated version in prepend merge (Keep a Changelog), consumed once for the newest version; generator-emitted Unreleased still replaces normally."
expected_result: Released changelog has no duplicate Unreleased section
actual_result: "No duplicate; 103 tests pass incl. 2 new merge tests; release:check green"
close_reason: Fixed in prepend-merge promotion logic
body: ""
